feesApply.feesApplyText:
Tenancy Information

What permitted payments can I expect to pay if I rent a property with Your Move?

When you have agreed on the property of your choice, Your Move will provide you with a Tenancy Application Form. This helps explain not only the next stages of your application but any permitted payments which are due before you sign your Tenancy Agreement and any which may become payable during and after the tenancy. This will also include confirmation of the agreed rent and the deposit.

Below is a list of our current permitted payments. At any time you are interested in a property, please ask a member of staff for a full breakdown of permitted payments that may be payable before, during and after a tenancy.

Holding Deposit (per tenancy) One week's rent.

This is to reserve a property. Please Note: This will be withheld if any relevant person (including any guarantor(s)) withdraw from the tenancy, fail a Right-to-Rent check, provide materially significant false or misleading information, or fail to sign their tenancy agreement (and / or Deed of Guarantee) within 15 calendar days (or other Deadline for Agreement as mutually agreed in writing).

Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent under £50,000 per year) Five weeks' rent.

This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy and applies to Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST).

Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent of £50,000 or over per year)

Six weeks' rent. This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy and applies to Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST).

Unpaid Rent.

Interest at 3% above the Bank of England Base Rate from Rent Due Date until paid in order to pursue non-payment of rent. Please Note: This will not be levied until the rent is more than 14 days in arrears.

Lost Key(s) or other Security Device(s).

Tenants are liable to the actual cost of replacing any lost key(s) or other security device(s). If the loss results in locks needing to be changed, the actual costs of a locksmith, new lock and replacement keys for the tenant, landlord any other persons requiring keys will be charged to the tenant. If extra costs are incurred there will be a charge of £15 per hour (inc. VAT) for the time taken replacing lost key(s) or other security device(s).

Variation of Contract (Tenant's Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per agreed variation.

To cover the costs associated with taking landlord's instructions as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.

Change of Sharer (Tenant's Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per replacement tenant or any reasonable costs incurred if higher.

To cover the costs associated with taking landlord's instructions, new tenant referencing and Right-to-Rent checks, deposit registration as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.

Early Termination (Tenant's Request).

Should the tenant wish to leave their contract early, they shall be liable to the landlord's costs in re-letting the property as well as all rent due under the tenancy until the start date of the replacement tenancy. These costs will be no more than the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy.

Client Money Protection is provided by Propertymark. Redress through The Property Ombudsman Scheme.

A brand new, top floor, two bedroom apartment located in the Town Centre and offering a private terrace with far reaching views over Maidstone.


DESCRIPTION
A brand new, top floor, two bedroom apartment located in the Town Centre and offering a private terrace with far reaching views over Maidstone.

This apartment is finished to a very high standad and is being let on an unfurnished basis. The accommodation comprises:

Entrace hallway with storage cupboard, spacious open plan living room with space for a dining area, modern fitted kitchen with integrated electric hob and oven, washing machine, dishwasher and fridge/freezer, main double bedroom, further double bedroom and modern bathroom with panel enclosed bath with shower over, low level wc and wash basin.

This apartment is priced at £1,350 pcm (without parking) or £1,450 pcm (with one parking space included).

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Acceptance of any offer will be subject to contract, referencing and immigration checks. You will need to pay the Rent and Deposit that is due under a Tenancy Agreement, or where the landlord is offering the property with a deposit replacement guarantee product, and you wish to take up this option, you will need to provide proof that you have purchased such a product by providing us with a copy of the insurance certificate before a tenancy can start.

Referencing and Right to Rent Checks - You will be asked to complete an application form before referencing can be undertaken, you should also provide an original photographic Identification (e.g. passport, National ID card, VISA, resident permit, driving licence) and Proof of Residence (e.g. original utility bill, council tax bill or bank statement all of which much be less than 3 months old). The need for a guarantor may not become apparent until your referencing (including references for any joint tenants) has been completed. Where a guarantor is required an application form and photographic identification with proof of residence will be required.

Referencing will cover a check against the credit file and public records of the individual, an Anti-Money Laundering check, confirmation of employment and salary details, confirmation of previous tenancy details, right to rent checks, reporting the results of all those checks to your prospective landlord to see if your application is acceptable.

Tenant deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Deposits are limited to the equivalent of 5 weeks rent for new and renewed tenancies (or 6 weeks if the annual rent is £50,000 or more). This is calculated by dividing the annual rent by 52 and multiplying by 5 (or 6 if rent is £50,000 or more) and will be required to be paid at the start of the tenancy. This is subject to referencing.

Holding deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Holding Deposits are limited to the equivalent of one weeks rent. This is paid in order to reserve a property. This is calculated by multiplying the monthly rent by 12 to establish the annual rent, then dividing the annual rent by 52. The Holding Deposit will be required to be paid once your offer is accepted. You will be provided with the rules of when this is to be returned to you or retained by the agent before this payment is made.

Tenant Fees Act 2019 permits certain fees / charges to be made under the following circumstances:

Fee£ Inc. VATExplanation
Default fee for late payment of rentChargeable from 14 days arrears calculated on the interest at 3% above Bank of England base rate on the late payment of rent for each day that the payment is outstanding.
Loss of a key or other security deviceLandlords and letting agents can charge a tenant a fee to cover the cost of replacing the lost key or security device (e.g. fob, electronic device for garage doors / security gates).
Payment on variation, assignment or novation of a tenancy£50.00 When a tenant has requested it, landlords and letting agents can charge to vary, assign or replace a tenancy. Fee charge £50 (including VAT)
Payment on termination of a tenancyLandlords and letting agents can require a tenant to make a payment for an early termination (surrender) of the tenancy agreement at the tenants request.
Company application fee£100.00 £100 including VAT

Should you require further clarification, please ask us to explain these to you.

We are members of:

The Property Ombudsman Redress Scheme - C0008

ARLA/Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme - C0002080

greenSpaces.content:
Maidstone boasts numerous green spaces and trails.

**Parks and Green Spaces**

*   **Mote Park:** A large central park with a lake, woodland, and grassland, easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Whatman Park:** Forming part of the Maidstone Millennium River Park, it features a rose garden and playgrounds and is easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Teston Bridge Country Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park with playgrounds, conveniently located by car, though slightly further from the town centre.
*   **Clare Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park.  Accessibility from the town centre is not detailed.
*   **Cobtree Manor Park:** A smaller country park ideal for walks and picnics.  Town centre accessibility is unspecified.
*   **Brenchley Gardens:** A small formal garden near Maidstone East Station, easily accessible on foot.

**Walking Trails**

*   **Maidstone Millennium River Park:** A 10km riverside path along the River Medway, traversing the town centre and easily accessible on foot.
*   **North Downs Way National Trail:**  Sections of this long-distance trail are accessible by car, requiring a walk from the access point.

**Mountain Biking Trails**

*   Various mountain biking trails of differing lengths and difficulty levels are located around Maidstone, best accessed by car.  Precise accessibility details are unavailable, but further information can be found on AllTrails and Trailforks.

publicTransport.content:
Maidstone benefits from convenient transport links.

**Rail Services**

*   Three stations serve Maidstone: Maidstone East, Maidstone West, and Maidstone Barracks, all served by Southeastern.
*   Maidstone East provides direct trains to London Victoria (under an hour), Ashford International, and Canterbury.
*   Maidstone West offers services to Strood and Paddock Wood.

**Bus Services**

*   Arriva is the primary bus operator, supplemented by other providers.
*   Extensive bus routes connect Maidstone with neighbouring towns and villages, including park and ride facilities.

**Other Transport**

*   Taxis offer convenient local and regional travel.
*   Road access is facilitated by the M2 and M20 motorways, providing links to the M25 and other major routes.  Numerous roads connect Maidstone to surrounding areas.  However, congestion is anticipated during peak times.  Information on dedicated cycle lanes was unavailable.

(Information accurate as of January 2025)

barsAndRestaurants.content:
Maidstone's hospitality scene (accurate as of January 2025) includes a variety of restaurants, bars and cafes.

**Restaurants**

A selection of restaurants includes Argentinian cuisine at Buenos Aires Nights; The Romney at Mote House; Cast Iron Grill; family dining at Harvester - Running Horse; and The White Horse - Bearsted.  Other options include The Horseshoes @ East Farleigh; Taj Mahal Authentic Indian; Dylan's Nepalese and Indian; Wildwood Maidstone (European and global dishes); Vesuvias Restaurant; The Bierkeller - Maidstone; KalaRED Oriental Bar Restaurant; Thai Orchid Maidstone; Frederic Bistro; Wagamama Maidstone; Giggling Squid Maidstone; Market House Maidstone; Zizzi Maidstone; Patisserie Valerie Maidstone; Thaipalace; and Fifi's Brasserie.


**Bars**

Numerous bars are available, including MuMu; Bar Chocolate; Source Bar; The Brenchley; The Muggleton Inn; The Market House; The Stag; The Ashes Bar; The Bull Maidstone; and Ballin' Maidstone.


**Cafes**

Coffee and food are available at The Old Boat Cafe and Ivy Coffee House (which also offers cakes, pastries, breakfast and lunch).  Other cafes include The Little Old Toll House; Leah's; Aunt Sallys Kitchen (homemade breakfast and lunch); Baskerville's Coffee House (tea, sandwiches and pastries); Esquires Coffee - Maidstone (coffee, smoothies and snacks); and BBs Coffee & Muffins (muffins, coffee and savoury food).

schoolsAndNurseries.content:
Maidstone offers a range of schooling options, making it a potentially attractive location for families.  This information is accurate as of January 2025, but parents should verify details directly with the schools.

**Highly-Rated Primary Schools**

*   **Jubilee Primary School:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted.
*   **Tree Tops Primary Academy:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and well-regarded.
*   **Archbishop Courtenay Primary School:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and highly-regarded.

**Highly-Rated Secondary Schools**

*   **Maidstone Grammar School for Girls:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a leading girls' grammar school.
*   **Invicta Grammar School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; an excellent grammar school.
*   **Bower Grove School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a top-performing secondary school.
*   **Five Acre Wood School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; another highly-rated secondary school.

**Additional Schooling Options**

*   Maidstone has numerous other primary and secondary schools, many with positive Ofsted reports.
*   Three independent schools - OneSchool Global UK Maidstone Campus, Sutton Valence School, and MEPA Academy - provide fee-paying alternatives.

Always consult Ofsted reports and individual school websites for the most current information.

fitnessAndGyms.content:
Maidstone, UK, offers a variety of fitness facilities as of January 2025.

**Gyms**

Several gyms are available, including Welcome Gym, Village Gym, CORE The Gym, and PureGym.  Facilities typically include a range of equipment, classes, and amenities such as swimming pools, saunas, and steam rooms.  Many offer flexible membership options and free parking; however, specific details should be verified on individual gym websites.

**Yoga Studios**

A number of yoga studios operate in the town, such as Heavenly Fitness Studios, Yoga With Nicola, and Flowstone Studio.  These studios provide various yoga styles, including Hatha and Vinyasa.  Class schedules and specific styles offered vary, so it is advisable to check individual studio websites.

**Swimming Pools**

Swimming facilities are available at Maidstone Leisure Centre (with a learner, leisure, and main pool), Lockmeadow Health Club, Village Gym, and a 20m pool at Freedom Leisure.  Opening times differ between facilities, so please check the relevant websites for details.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Tenancy Information

What permitted payments can I expect to pay if I rent a property with Your Move?

When you have agreed on the property of your choice, Your Move will provide you with a Tenancy Application Form. This helps explain not only the next stages of your application but any permitted payments which are due before you sign your Tenancy Agreement and any which may become payable during and after the tenancy. This will also include confirmation of the agreed rent and the deposit.

Below is a list of our current permitted payments. At any time you are interested in a property, please ask a member of staff for a full breakdown of permitted payments that may be payable before, during and after a tenancy.

Holding Deposit (per tenancy) One week's rent.

This is to reserve a property. Please Note: This will be withheld if any relevant person (including any guarantor(s)) withdraw from the tenancy, fail a Right-to-Rent check, provide materially significant false or misleading information, or fail to sign their tenancy agreement (and / or Deed of Guarantee) within 15 calendar days (or other Deadline for Agreement as mutually agreed in writing).

Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent under £50,000 per year) Five weeks' rent.

This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy and applies to Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST).

Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent of £50,000 or over per year)

Six weeks' rent. This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy and applies to Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST).

Unpaid Rent.

Interest at 3% above the Bank of England Base Rate from Rent Due Date until paid in order to pursue non-payment of rent. Please Note: This will not be levied until the rent is more than 14 days in arrears.

Lost Key(s) or other Security Device(s).

Tenants are liable to the actual cost of replacing any lost key(s) or other security device(s). If the loss results in locks needing to be changed, the actual costs of a locksmith, new lock and replacement keys for the tenant, landlord any other persons requiring keys will be charged to the tenant. If extra costs are incurred there will be a charge of £15 per hour (inc. VAT) for the time taken replacing lost key(s) or other security device(s).

Variation of Contract (Tenant's Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per agreed variation.

To cover the costs associated with taking landlord's instructions as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.

Change of Sharer (Tenant's Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per replacement tenant or any reasonable costs incurred if higher.

To cover the costs associated with taking landlord's instructions, new tenant referencing and Right-to-Rent checks, deposit registration as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.

Early Termination (Tenant's Request).

Should the tenant wish to leave their contract early, they shall be liable to the landlord's costs in re-letting the property as well as all rent due under the tenancy until the start date of the replacement tenancy. These costs will be no more than the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy.

Client Money Protection is provided by Propertymark. Redress through The Property Ombudsman Scheme.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Tenant Fees: Assured Shorthold Tenancies
Holding Deposit (per tenancy) One weeks rent.
This is to reserve a property. Please Note: This will be withheld if any relevant person (including any guarantor(s)) withdraw from the tenancy, fail a Right to Rent check provide materially significant false or misleading information or fail to sign their tenancy agreement (and / or Deed of Guarantee) within 15 calendar days (or other Deadline for Agreement as mutually agreed in writing).
Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent under £50,000 per year) Five weeks rent.
This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy.
Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent of £50,000 or over per year) Six weeks rent.
This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy.
Unpaid Rent
Interest at 3% above the Bank of England Base Rate from Rent Due Date until paid in order to pursue non-payment of rent. Please Note: This will not be levied until the rent is more than 14 days in arrears.
Lost Key(s) or other Security Device(s)
Tenants are liable to the actual cost of replacing any lost key(s) or other security device(s). If the loss results in locks needing to be changed, the actual costs of a locksmith, new lock and replacement keys for the tenant, landlord any other persons requiring keys will be charged to the tenant. If extra costs are incurred there will be a charge of £10 per hour (inc. VAT) for the time taken replacing lost key(s) or other security device(s).
Variation of Contract (Tenant s Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per agreed variation.
To cover the costs associated with taking landlords instructions as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.
Change of Sharer (Tenant s Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per replacement tenant or any reasonable costs incurred if higher.
To cover the costs associated with taking landlords instructions, new tenant referencing and Right-to-Rent checks, deposit registration as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.
Early Termination (Tenants Request)
Should the tenant wish to leave their contract early, they shall be liable to the landlord s costs in re-letting the property as well as all rent due under the tenancy until the start date of the replacement tenancy. These costs will be no more than the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy.
COMPANY LETS
BEFORE YOU MOVE IN
Application & Referencing Fee: £300 (inc VAT)
Rent In Advance Payment Administration Fee: £24 (inc VAT)
Right To Rent Checks: £6 (inc VAT) per adult moving into the property
Check-Out Fee: £118.80 (inc VAT)
Deposit: Usually the equivalent of 6 weeks rent (Rent x 12 divide by 52 x 6)
Abort / Withdrawal Fee: £300 (inc VAT, maximum fee)
DURING YOUR TENANCY
Amendment Fee: £150 (inc VAT) Per Amendment
Renewal Fee: £96 (inc VAT)
OTHER FEES AND CHARGES
Aborted Appointment Fee: £48 (inc VAT)
Early Release Fee: £90 (inc VAT) + Landlord Reletting Costs
Client Money Protection: Propertymark
Independent Redress: The Property Ombudsman
IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS ON OUR FEES, PLEASE ASK A MEMBER OF OUR LETTINGS TEAM

text.description:
Property Reference: 2427468.

This property is a stunning one-bedroom flat in a prime, highly sort after, location on the south side of Royal Tunbridge Wells. Cedars is within walking distance of the famous Pantiles, High Street shops, cafes, pubs, bars and railway station. The property has the best of all worlds being perfectly located for all town amenities and surrounded by countryside – Tunbridge Wells Common, Hargate Forest and the Tunbridge Wells Circular Walk. The property is located up a quiet lane and is surrounded by a large communal garden and driveway (with 1 designated parking space and visitor bays). The property is accessed via a communal entrance and has its own front door and staircase leading to the second level. It is the only flat on this floor, ensuring excellent sound proofing, and spans the whole length of the building. The property has large and naturally light rooms with velux windows throughout. There is plenty of storage with a walk-in storage cupboard and fitted wardrobes. The property is being offered furnished with luxury fittings such as a 50” SMART Samsung TV and a super king bed with memory foam mattress. It has a unique and spacious layout that also includes a sofa bed for any guests. The kitchen includes a gas hob, electric fan oven, large fridge/freezer, washer/dryer machine, dishwasher, large microwave oven, toaster and kettle. This property has been a much-loved home and has come to the rental market whilst the landlords emigrate. It is one not to be missed and will provide any clean, tidy professional single or couple a delightful place to live. 



Summary & Exclusions:
- Rent Amount: £1,400.00 per month (£323.08 per week)
- Deposit / Bond: £1,615.38
- 1 Bedrooms
- 1 Bathrooms
- Property comes furnished
- Available to move in from 03 May, 2025
- Minimum tenancy term is 6 months
- Maximum number of tenants is 2
- No Students
- No Pets, sorry
- No Smokers
- Not Suitable for Families / Children
- Bills not included
- Property has parking
- Property has garden access
- EPC Rating: C

If calling, please quote reference: 2427468

Fees:
You will not be charged any admin fees.


** Contact today to book a viewing and have the landlord show you round! **

text.description:
Nestled on Dale Street in Dartford, this delightful two bedroom coach house offers the perfect blend of comfort and convenience. Spanning two floors, the property features two generously sized bedrooms and two stylish bathrooms, ideal for modern living. The inviting living room provides a warm and welcoming space to unwind, while the modern kitchen is designed for both practicality and style, making meal preparation effortless. Combining contemporary comforts with classic charm, this home is a wonderful choice for those seeking a peaceful yet well-connected residence.

Excellent Connectivity:
Located just a short distance from Dartford Train Station, this property offers superb transport links, with regular services to London Charing Cross and London Victoria. The nearby A2 and M25 ensure seamless access to central London and surrounding areas, while local bus routes further enhance travel convenience.

Vibrant Local Scene:
Dartford boasts a lively community with a wealth of amenities and attractions. From the shopping and dining experiences at Bluewater Shopping Centre to the cultural performances at the Orchard Theatre, there’s something for everyone. Nature lovers will appreciate the scenic Dartford Central Park, perfect for leisurely walks and outdoor activities. With its welcoming atmosphere and diverse lifestyle offerings, this location is an exceptional place to call home.

This property is available with a Deposit Free option which means that instead of paying a traditional five weeks security deposit, you pay a fee of one weeks rent + VAT (subject to a minimum of £120 + VAT) to become a member of a deposit free renting scheme which significantly reduces the up-front costs. This fee is non-refundable and is not a deposit so cannot be used towards covering the cost of any future damage.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
As well as paying the rent, you may also be required to make the following permitted payments. Permitted payments For properties in England, the Tenant Fees Act 2019 means that in addition to rent, lettings agents can only charge tenants (or anyone acting on the tenant's behalf) the following permitted payments:
  • Holding deposits (a maximum of 1 week's rent);
  • Deposits (a maximum deposit of 5 weeks' rent for annual rent below £50,000, or 6 weeks' rent for annual rental of £50,000 and above);
  • Payments to change a tenancy agreement eg. change of sharer (capped at £50 or, if higher, any reasonable costs);
  • Payments associated with early termination of a tenancy (capped at the landlord's loss or the agent's reasonably incurred costs);
  • Where required, utilities (electricity, gas or other fuel, water, sewerage), communication services "telephone, internet, cable/satellite television), TV licence;
  • Council tax (payable to the billing authority);
  • Interest payments for the late payment of rent (up to 3% above Bank of England's annual percentage rate);
  • Reasonable costs for replacement of lost keys or other security devices;
  • Contractual damages in the event of the tenant's default of a tenancy agreement; and
  • Any other permitted payments under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 and regulations applicable at the relevant time.
For properties in Wales, the Renting Homes (Fees etc.) (Wales) Act 2019 means that in addition to rent, lettings agents can only charge tenants the following permitted payments
  • Holding deposits (a maximum of 1 week's rent);
  • Security deposits;
  • Where required, utilities (electricity, gas or other fuel, water, sewerage), communication services "telephone, internet, cable/satellite television), TV licence;
  • Council tax (payable to the billing authority);
  • Payments for the late payment of rent (where required under the tenancy agreement);
  • A breach of a term of the contract (where required under the tenancy agreement); and
  • Any other permitted payments under the Renting Homes (Fees etc.) (Wales) Act and regulations applicable at the relevant time.
Tenant protection In addition to publishing relevant fees, lettings agents are also required to publish details of:
  • the redress scheme they are a member of; and
  • the name of the approved or designated Client Money Protection scheme they are a member of (if any).

feesApply.feesApplyText:
FEES IN RELATION TO TENANCY AGREEMENTS SIGNED ON OR AFTER 1ST JUNE 2019
HOLDING DEPOSIT
- Equivalent to one week's rent per tenancy (annual rent amount divided by 52)
- The property will be reserved on payment of the Holding Deposit
- The Deadline for Agreement is 15 calendar days after the Holding Deposit is paid unless an "extension" date is agreed in writing by the tenant
The Holding Deposit will be refunded to the tenant within 7 days:-
(i) from when the parties enter into the tenancy agreement unless the tenant has agreed in writing for the Holding Deposit to be put towards the balance of monies payable
(ii) if the landlord withdraws
(iii) if an agreement is not reached before the Deadline for Agreement or the agreed extended date and the tenant is not at fault, or
(iv) if the landlord or the agent breaches the fee ban or acts in a way that it would be unreasonable to expect the tenant to enter into a tenancy agreement (i.e. unfair terms, harassment etc)
The Agent can retain the Holding Deposit only if:
(i) the tenant withdraws their application
(ii) the tenant doesn't take reasonable steps to enter into the tenancy
(iii) the tenant fails a Right to Rent check
(iv) the tenant provides false or misleading information which materially affects their suitability to rent the property
RENT
- The amount which will be contractually payable to rent the property at regular specified intervals.
SECURITY DEPOSIT
- Equivalent to five weeks' rent per tenancy if rent is less than £50,000 per year
- Equivalent to six weeks' rent per tenancy if rent is more than £50,000 per year
- The Security Deposit can be used to cover damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy
- Where the Zero Deposit product is available tenants will be required to pay a figure equivalent to one weeks rent rather than a cash deposit as stated above. Zero Deposit is available subject to terms and conditions.
- Interest is payable by the tenant on late rent at the rate of 3% above the Bank of England Base Rate in relation to each day after the due date for which the rent is unpaid but not to be levied until the rent is more than 14 days in arrears
UTILITIES & COUNCIL TAX
- Gas, electricity, fuel, water or sewage, communication services, television licence, Green Deal charge (if any) and council tax
LOST KEY / ACCESS OR SECURITY DEVICE
- The cost of replacement including the cost of replacement of the locks (if applicable)
VARIATION OF CONTRACT
- £50 (including VAT) per agreed variation at the tenant's request to include the cost of the preparation and execution of new documentation
- £50 (including VAT) per agreed replacement tenant at the tenant's request to include the cost of Right to Rent checks, deposit registration and the preparation and execution of new legal documents
- £50 (including VAT) per agreed variation at the tenant's request to keep a pet at the property
EARLY TERMINATION
- If the tenant wishes to leave the contract early and there is no break clause, the tenant shall pay the rent until the start date of any replacement tenancy together with the landlord's re-letting costs (in accordance with Acorn's published landlord letting fees); such costs to be no more than the
maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy
----
PEACE OF MIND
The Acorn Group are part The Ombudsman Redress Scheme and are a member of the Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme. Tenant deposits are protected by the Tenancy Deposit Scheme.
For more information please contact your local branch.

Property Description: Hartlip Close, Sheerness, Kent, ME12 1JG

Nestled in a peaceful and sought-after location, Hartlip Close is a beautifully presented mid-terraced 3-bedroom house offering the perfect balance of modern living and picturesque surroundings. Ideal for families or anyone looking to enjoy a serene lifestyle, this property is ready to welcome its new owners.

Key Features:

3 Spacious Bedrooms: Generously sized rooms, perfect for family living or creating your own home office or guest room.
Large Garden: The property boasts a substantial garden, offering plenty of space for outdoor activities, entertaining, or simply unwinding in the fresh air. Imagine hosting BBQs, gardening, or enjoying the views in this private outdoor space.
Breathtaking Countryside Views: Wake up every day to the calming sights of beautiful countryside, providing a tranquil escape from the hustle and bustle of everyday life. Perfect for those who appreciate nature's beauty.
Modern Interior: The home offers a light, airy, and practical layout, providing a comfortable living space for any family. The well-maintained interior is ready for you to move in and make it your own.
Quiet and Peaceful Location: Located in a quiet cul-de-sac, yet with easy access to local amenities, schools, and transport links. It offers the best of both worlds - a peaceful retreat with everything you need just a short distance away.
Off-Street Parking: For added convenience, the property includes off-street parking, ensuring a hassle-free arrival every time you come home.
Location:
Hartlip Close is perfectly positioned in Sheerness, Kent, where you can enjoy the tranquility of countryside views, but still benefit from being within easy reach of local shops, schools, and excellent transport links. Sheerness is renowned for its coastal charm and scenic surroundings, making it an ideal location for families, professionals, and nature lovers alike.

Whether you're seeking a relaxing retreat to call home or a spacious family abode, this 3-bedroom house has everything you need. Don't miss the chance to make this property your own - click to view more details and arrange a viewing today!

Your new home awaits!

greenSpaces.content:
Maidstone boasts numerous green spaces and trails.

**Parks and Green Spaces**

*   **Mote Park:** A large central park with a lake, woodland, and grassland, easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Whatman Park:** Forming part of the Maidstone Millennium River Park, it features a rose garden and playgrounds and is easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Teston Bridge Country Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park with playgrounds, conveniently located by car, though slightly further from the town centre.
*   **Clare Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park.  Accessibility from the town centre is not detailed.
*   **Cobtree Manor Park:** A smaller country park ideal for walks and picnics.  Town centre accessibility is unspecified.
*   **Brenchley Gardens:** A small formal garden near Maidstone East Station, easily accessible on foot.

**Walking Trails**

*   **Maidstone Millennium River Park:** A 10km riverside path along the River Medway, traversing the town centre and easily accessible on foot.
*   **North Downs Way National Trail:**  Sections of this long-distance trail are accessible by car, requiring a walk from the access point.

**Mountain Biking Trails**

*   Various mountain biking trails of differing lengths and difficulty levels are located around Maidstone, best accessed by car.  Precise accessibility details are unavailable, but further information can be found on AllTrails and Trailforks.

publicTransport.content:
Maidstone benefits from convenient transport links.

**Rail Services**

*   Three stations serve Maidstone: Maidstone East, Maidstone West, and Maidstone Barracks, all served by Southeastern.
*   Maidstone East provides direct trains to London Victoria (under an hour), Ashford International, and Canterbury.
*   Maidstone West offers services to Strood and Paddock Wood.

**Bus Services**

*   Arriva is the primary bus operator, supplemented by other providers.
*   Extensive bus routes connect Maidstone with neighbouring towns and villages, including park and ride facilities.

**Other Transport**

*   Taxis offer convenient local and regional travel.
*   Road access is facilitated by the M2 and M20 motorways, providing links to the M25 and other major routes.  Numerous roads connect Maidstone to surrounding areas.  However, congestion is anticipated during peak times.  Information on dedicated cycle lanes was unavailable.

(Information accurate as of January 2025)

barsAndRestaurants.content:
Maidstone's hospitality scene (accurate as of January 2025) includes a variety of restaurants, bars and cafes.

**Restaurants**

A selection of restaurants includes Argentinian cuisine at Buenos Aires Nights; The Romney at Mote House; Cast Iron Grill; family dining at Harvester - Running Horse; and The White Horse - Bearsted.  Other options include The Horseshoes @ East Farleigh; Taj Mahal Authentic Indian; Dylan's Nepalese and Indian; Wildwood Maidstone (European and global dishes); Vesuvias Restaurant; The Bierkeller - Maidstone; KalaRED Oriental Bar Restaurant; Thai Orchid Maidstone; Frederic Bistro; Wagamama Maidstone; Giggling Squid Maidstone; Market House Maidstone; Zizzi Maidstone; Patisserie Valerie Maidstone; Thaipalace; and Fifi's Brasserie.


**Bars**

Numerous bars are available, including MuMu; Bar Chocolate; Source Bar; The Brenchley; The Muggleton Inn; The Market House; The Stag; The Ashes Bar; The Bull Maidstone; and Ballin' Maidstone.


**Cafes**

Coffee and food are available at The Old Boat Cafe and Ivy Coffee House (which also offers cakes, pastries, breakfast and lunch).  Other cafes include The Little Old Toll House; Leah's; Aunt Sallys Kitchen (homemade breakfast and lunch); Baskerville's Coffee House (tea, sandwiches and pastries); Esquires Coffee - Maidstone (coffee, smoothies and snacks); and BBs Coffee & Muffins (muffins, coffee and savoury food).

schoolsAndNurseries.content:
Maidstone offers a range of schooling options, making it a potentially attractive location for families.  This information is accurate as of January 2025, but parents should verify details directly with the schools.

**Highly-Rated Primary Schools**

*   **Jubilee Primary School:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted.
*   **Tree Tops Primary Academy:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and well-regarded.
*   **Archbishop Courtenay Primary School:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and highly-regarded.

**Highly-Rated Secondary Schools**

*   **Maidstone Grammar School for Girls:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a leading girls' grammar school.
*   **Invicta Grammar School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; an excellent grammar school.
*   **Bower Grove School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a top-performing secondary school.
*   **Five Acre Wood School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; another highly-rated secondary school.

**Additional Schooling Options**

*   Maidstone has numerous other primary and secondary schools, many with positive Ofsted reports.
*   Three independent schools - OneSchool Global UK Maidstone Campus, Sutton Valence School, and MEPA Academy - provide fee-paying alternatives.

Always consult Ofsted reports and individual school websites for the most current information.

fitnessAndGyms.content:
Maidstone, UK, offers a variety of fitness facilities as of January 2025.

**Gyms**

Several gyms are available, including Welcome Gym, Village Gym, CORE The Gym, and PureGym.  Facilities typically include a range of equipment, classes, and amenities such as swimming pools, saunas, and steam rooms.  Many offer flexible membership options and free parking; however, specific details should be verified on individual gym websites.

**Yoga Studios**

A number of yoga studios operate in the town, such as Heavenly Fitness Studios, Yoga With Nicola, and Flowstone Studio.  These studios provide various yoga styles, including Hatha and Vinyasa.  Class schedules and specific styles offered vary, so it is advisable to check individual studio websites.

**Swimming Pools**

Swimming facilities are available at Maidstone Leisure Centre (with a learner, leisure, and main pool), Lockmeadow Health Club, Village Gym, and a 20m pool at Freedom Leisure.  Opening times differ between facilities, so please check the relevant websites for details.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Acceptance of any offer will be subject to contract, referencing and immigration checks. You will need to pay the Rent and Deposit that is due under a Tenancy Agreement, or where the landlord is offering the property with a deposit replacement guarantee product, and you wish to take up this option, you will need to provide proof that you have purchased such a product by providing us with a copy of the insurance certificate before a tenancy can start.

Referencing and Right to Rent Checks - You will be asked to complete an application form before referencing can be undertaken, you should also provide an original photographic Identification (e.g. passport, National ID card, VISA, resident permit, driving licence) and Proof of Residence (e.g. original utility bill, council tax bill or bank statement all of which much be less than 3 months old). The need for a guarantor may not become apparent until your referencing (including references for any joint tenants) has been completed. Where a guarantor is required an application form and photographic identification with proof of residence will be required.

Referencing will cover a check against the credit file and public records of the individual, an Anti-Money Laundering check, confirmation of employment and salary details, confirmation of previous tenancy details, right to rent checks, reporting the results of all those checks to your prospective landlord to see if your application is acceptable.

Tenant deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Deposits are limited to the equivalent of 5 weeks rent for new and renewed tenancies (or 6 weeks if the annual rent is £50,000 or more). This is calculated by dividing the annual rent by 52 and multiplying by 5 (or 6 if rent is £50,000 or more) and will be required to be paid at the start of the tenancy. This is subject to referencing.

Holding deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Holding Deposits are limited to the equivalent of one weeks rent. This is paid in order to reserve a property. This is calculated by multiplying the monthly rent by 12 to establish the annual rent, then dividing the annual rent by 52. The Holding Deposit will be required to be paid once your offer is accepted. You will be provided with the rules of when this is to be returned to you or retained by the agent before this payment is made.

Tenant Fees Act 2019 permits certain fees / charges to be made under the following circumstances:

Fee£ Inc. VATExplanation
Default fee for late payment of rentChargeable from 14 days arrears calculated on the interest at 3% above Bank of England base rate on the late payment of rent for each day that the payment is outstanding.
Loss of a key or other security deviceLandlords and letting agents can charge a tenant a fee to cover the cost of replacing the lost key or security device (e.g. fob, electronic device for garage doors / security gates).
Payment on variation, assignment or novation of a tenancy£50.00 When a tenant has requested it, landlords and letting agents can charge to vary, assign or replace a tenancy. Fee charge £50 (including VAT)
Payment on termination of a tenancyLandlords and letting agents can require a tenant to make a payment for an early termination (surrender) of the tenancy agreement at the tenants request.
Company application fee£100.00 £100 including VAT

Should you require further clarification, please ask us to explain these to you.

We are members of:

The Property Ombudsman Redress Scheme - C0008

ARLA/Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme - C0002080

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Tenant's Schedule of Fees
For any tenant renting a home under an Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST) the following are payable or potentially payable:
* A holding deposit of one week's rent to reserve a property which will then be allocated towards the first month's rent.
* The security deposit, equivalent to five weeks' rent, rising to six week's rent when the annual rent is in excess of £50,000.
* The rent and utility bills as outlined in the Tenancy Agreement.
* Unpaid rent will potentially incur interest at 3% above the Bank of England base rate, as outlined in the Tenancy Agreement.
* Tenants are liable for the cost of replacing any lost keys or security device, including a change of lock or replacement of device if required.
* Amendments of Tenancy Agreement at tenants request (£50 per change).
* Should a tenant need to surrender the tenancy early and the Landlord agrees to re-let the property, the liability for the payment of rent will end once a new tenant is found and takes up occupation. However, the tenant will still need to cover the Landlord's costs in surrendering the tenancy and re-letting the property.
* Where an out of hours call out is applicable this will be charged at £15 per hour incl. VAT. Normal business hours are Monday to Friday 9am to 6pm and Saturday 9am to 4pm, therefore out of hours is considered outside of these times.
* Should a tenant wish to make changes to the contract (a written variation of contract) such as permission for a pet, to redecorate, to sublet - then a fee of £50 incl. VAT or reasonable costs if higher will be applicable.
For any individual tenant not renting a property under an Assured Shorthold Tenancy the following charges are also payable:
* Tenant reference charge (£60 per tenant incl. VAT) covers collecting and verifying references from employer/accountant and previous landlord references, as well as carrying out a credit check and collecting a copy of passport, proof of residency, bank statements and a recent payslip.
* Guarantor charge (£60 incl. VAT per guarantor if required) covers credit referencing and preparing a Letter of Guarantee as part of the Tenancy Agreement.
* Professional check-in fee (£150 incl VAT) enables us to arrange a date and time with the tenant to be checked in at the start of the tenancy and checked out at the end of the tenancy, instruct inventory providers, agree the terms of the security deposit disbursement between Landlord and tenant, return deposit as agreed with the Landlord and tenant to relevant parties, remit any disputed amount to the Tenancy Deposit Scheme for final adjudication, unprotect security deposit, instruct contractors and obtain quotes, organise repairs/replacements/cost of any broken or missing items.
All prices are inclusive of VAT.
Rest assured, as a member of The Property Ombudsman (TPO) for lettings we subscribe to TPO's Codes of Practice. This Government approved independent redress scheme gives consumers additional protection beyond that required by law. Our clients and customers have peace of mind that there is free and fair redress available in the unlikely event of an unresolved dispute involving our agency. Our membership number is: D10779
As regulated members of CMP this means that any monies we hold is insured. This gives our clients peace of mind and financial protection that their money will always be safe in our hands under the CMP Client Money Protection Scheme. Our membership number is: CMP002628

text.description:
This impressive end of terrace house is currently on the market for rent and is in a neutrally decorated condition. The property boasts a total of three open-plan reception rooms, one kitchen, three double bedrooms, and a bathroom. The reception rooms are a particular highlight. The first is a splendid open-plan room enjoying views of the garden, with built-in storage and direct access to the garden. The second reception room is separate, featuring large windows and elegant wood floors. The third reception room is also separate, with access to the garden and an inviting view of the outdoors.

Each of the three bedrooms is a double, offering ample space for personal comfort and furnishings. The bathroom is equipped with a modern shower facility. The kitchen offers a cheerful atmosphere with an abundance of natural light.

The property comes with some unique features, including a basement, a conservatory, and a garden. These add to the property's charm and make it even more appealing. The open-plan design of the property adds a sense of spaciousness and freedom, enhancing the overall appeal of the home.

Located ideally for families, the property is in close proximity to public transport links, schools, local amenities, and parks. This makes it a convenient place to live, ensuring you have everything you need nearby.

This property provides an excellent rental opportunity for families looking for a spacious, well-located home. It offers the perfect blend of comfort, convenience, and charm.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Tenancy Information

What permitted payments can I expect to pay if I rent a property with Your Move?

When you have agreed on the property of your choice, Your Move will provide you with a Tenancy Application Form. This helps explain not only the next stages of your application but any permitted payments which are due before you sign your Tenancy Agreement and any which may become payable during and after the tenancy. This will also include confirmation of the agreed rent and the deposit.

Below is a list of our current permitted payments. At any time you are interested in a property, please ask a member of staff for a full breakdown of permitted payments that may be payable before, during and after a tenancy.

Holding Deposit (per tenancy) One week's rent.

This is to reserve a property. Please Note: This will be withheld if any relevant person (including any guarantor(s)) withdraw from the tenancy, fail a Right-to-Rent check, provide materially significant false or misleading information, or fail to sign their tenancy agreement (and / or Deed of Guarantee) within 15 calendar days (or other Deadline for Agreement as mutually agreed in writing).

Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent under £50,000 per year) Five weeks' rent.

This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy and applies to Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST).

Security Deposit (per tenancy. Rent of £50,000 or over per year)

Six weeks' rent. This covers damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy and applies to Assured Shorthold Tenancies (AST).

Unpaid Rent.

Interest at 3% above the Bank of England Base Rate from Rent Due Date until paid in order to pursue non-payment of rent. Please Note: This will not be levied until the rent is more than 14 days in arrears.

Lost Key(s) or other Security Device(s).

Tenants are liable to the actual cost of replacing any lost key(s) or other security device(s). If the loss results in locks needing to be changed, the actual costs of a locksmith, new lock and replacement keys for the tenant, landlord any other persons requiring keys will be charged to the tenant. If extra costs are incurred there will be a charge of £15 per hour (inc. VAT) for the time taken replacing lost key(s) or other security device(s).

Variation of Contract (Tenant's Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per agreed variation.

To cover the costs associated with taking landlord's instructions as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.

Change of Sharer (Tenant's Request) £50 (inc. VAT) per replacement tenant or any reasonable costs incurred if higher.

To cover the costs associated with taking landlord's instructions, new tenant referencing and Right-to-Rent checks, deposit registration as well as the preparation and execution of new legal documents.

Early Termination (Tenant's Request).

Should the tenant wish to leave their contract early, they shall be liable to the landlord's costs in re-letting the property as well as all rent due under the tenancy until the start date of the replacement tenancy. These costs will be no more than the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy.

Client Money Protection is provided by Propertymark. Redress through The Property Ombudsman Scheme.

Permitted payments
For properties in England, the Tenant Fees Act 2019 means that in addition to rent, lettings agents can only charge tenants (or anyone acting on the tenant's behalf) the following permitted payments:

Holding deposits (a maximum of 1 week's rent);
Deposits (a maximum deposit of 5 weeks' rent for annual rent below £50,000, or 6 weeks' rent for annual rental of £50,000 and above);
Payments to change a tenancy agreement eg. change of sharer (capped at £50 or, if higher, any reasonable costs);
Payments associated with early termination of a tenancy (capped at the landlord's loss or the agent's reasonably incurred costs);
Utilities, communication services (eg. telephone, broadband), TV licence and council tax;

This property is ready to move into and provides a welcoming and comfortable living space throughout.

The ground floor features a bright and airy lounge, creating the perfect space for relaxing or entertaining guests.

The kitchen is well-equipped with plenty of storage, ideal for everyday cooking, and leads to a separate dining room at the rear, offering additional space for family meals or social gatherings.

Upstairs, you'll find two generously-sized double bedrooms, each designed to maximise space and comfort.

The family bathroom is fitted with modern fixtures and provides a fresh, contemporary feel.

Externally, the property benefits from a private, low-maintenance courtyard garden—ideal for outdoor dining, relaxing, or enjoying sunny days. Council Tax Band: C Holding Deposit: £323.00

Not only does Ashton Burkinshaw have a network of offices across Kent and Sussex, but, we are also part of the Countrywide Group, the UK's largest residential property group with over 1,300 associated offices nationwide. greenSpaces.content:
Maidstone boasts numerous green spaces and trails.

**Parks and Green Spaces**

*   **Mote Park:** A large central park with a lake, woodland, and grassland, easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Whatman Park:** Forming part of the Maidstone Millennium River Park, it features a rose garden and playgrounds and is easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Teston Bridge Country Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park with playgrounds, conveniently located by car, though slightly further from the town centre.
*   **Clare Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park.  Accessibility from the town centre is not detailed.
*   **Cobtree Manor Park:** A smaller country park ideal for walks and picnics.  Town centre accessibility is unspecified.
*   **Brenchley Gardens:** A small formal garden near Maidstone East Station, easily accessible on foot.

**Walking Trails**

*   **Maidstone Millennium River Park:** A 10km riverside path along the River Medway, traversing the town centre and easily accessible on foot.
*   **North Downs Way National Trail:**  Sections of this long-distance trail are accessible by car, requiring a walk from the access point.

**Mountain Biking Trails**

*   Various mountain biking trails of differing lengths and difficulty levels are located around Maidstone, best accessed by car.  Precise accessibility details are unavailable, but further information can be found on AllTrails and Trailforks.

publicTransport.content:
Maidstone benefits from convenient transport links.

**Rail Services**

*   Three stations serve Maidstone: Maidstone East, Maidstone West, and Maidstone Barracks, all served by Southeastern.
*   Maidstone East provides direct trains to London Victoria (under an hour), Ashford International, and Canterbury.
*   Maidstone West offers services to Strood and Paddock Wood.

**Bus Services**

*   Arriva is the primary bus operator, supplemented by other providers.
*   Extensive bus routes connect Maidstone with neighbouring towns and villages, including park and ride facilities.

**Other Transport**

*   Taxis offer convenient local and regional travel.
*   Road access is facilitated by the M2 and M20 motorways, providing links to the M25 and other major routes.  Numerous roads connect Maidstone to surrounding areas.  However, congestion is anticipated during peak times.  Information on dedicated cycle lanes was unavailable.

(Information accurate as of January 2025)

barsAndRestaurants.content:
Maidstone's hospitality scene (accurate as of January 2025) includes a variety of restaurants, bars and cafes.

**Restaurants**

A selection of restaurants includes Argentinian cuisine at Buenos Aires Nights; The Romney at Mote House; Cast Iron Grill; family dining at Harvester - Running Horse; and The White Horse - Bearsted.  Other options include The Horseshoes @ East Farleigh; Taj Mahal Authentic Indian; Dylan's Nepalese and Indian; Wildwood Maidstone (European and global dishes); Vesuvias Restaurant; The Bierkeller - Maidstone; KalaRED Oriental Bar Restaurant; Thai Orchid Maidstone; Frederic Bistro; Wagamama Maidstone; Giggling Squid Maidstone; Market House Maidstone; Zizzi Maidstone; Patisserie Valerie Maidstone; Thaipalace; and Fifi's Brasserie.


**Bars**

Numerous bars are available, including MuMu; Bar Chocolate; Source Bar; The Brenchley; The Muggleton Inn; The Market House; The Stag; The Ashes Bar; The Bull Maidstone; and Ballin' Maidstone.


**Cafes**

Coffee and food are available at The Old Boat Cafe and Ivy Coffee House (which also offers cakes, pastries, breakfast and lunch).  Other cafes include The Little Old Toll House; Leah's; Aunt Sallys Kitchen (homemade breakfast and lunch); Baskerville's Coffee House (tea, sandwiches and pastries); Esquires Coffee - Maidstone (coffee, smoothies and snacks); and BBs Coffee & Muffins (muffins, coffee and savoury food).

schoolsAndNurseries.content:
Maidstone offers a range of schooling options, making it a potentially attractive location for families.  This information is accurate as of January 2025, but parents should verify details directly with the schools.

**Highly-Rated Primary Schools**

*   **Jubilee Primary School:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted.
*   **Tree Tops Primary Academy:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and well-regarded.
*   **Archbishop Courtenay Primary School:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and highly-regarded.

**Highly-Rated Secondary Schools**

*   **Maidstone Grammar School for Girls:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a leading girls' grammar school.
*   **Invicta Grammar School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; an excellent grammar school.
*   **Bower Grove School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a top-performing secondary school.
*   **Five Acre Wood School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; another highly-rated secondary school.

**Additional Schooling Options**

*   Maidstone has numerous other primary and secondary schools, many with positive Ofsted reports.
*   Three independent schools - OneSchool Global UK Maidstone Campus, Sutton Valence School, and MEPA Academy - provide fee-paying alternatives.

Always consult Ofsted reports and individual school websites for the most current information.

fitnessAndGyms.content:
Maidstone, UK, offers a variety of fitness facilities as of January 2025.

**Gyms**

Several gyms are available, including Welcome Gym, Village Gym, CORE The Gym, and PureGym.  Facilities typically include a range of equipment, classes, and amenities such as swimming pools, saunas, and steam rooms.  Many offer flexible membership options and free parking; however, specific details should be verified on individual gym websites.

**Yoga Studios**

A number of yoga studios operate in the town, such as Heavenly Fitness Studios, Yoga With Nicola, and Flowstone Studio.  These studios provide various yoga styles, including Hatha and Vinyasa.  Class schedules and specific styles offered vary, so it is advisable to check individual studio websites.

**Swimming Pools**

Swimming facilities are available at Maidstone Leisure Centre (with a learner, leisure, and main pool), Lockmeadow Health Club, Village Gym, and a 20m pool at Freedom Leisure.  Opening times differ between facilities, so please check the relevant websites for details.

As well as paying the rent, you may also be required to make the following permitted payments. Permitted payments For properties in England, the Tenant Fees Act 2019 means that in addition to rent, lettings agents can only charge tenants (or anyone acting on the tenant's behalf) the following permitted payments:
  • Holding deposits (a maximum of 1 week's rent);
  • Deposits (a maximum deposit of 5 weeks' rent for annual rent below £50,000, or 6 weeks' rent for annual rental of £50,000 and above);
  • Payments to change a tenancy agreement eg. change of sharer (capped at £50 or, if higher, any reasonable costs);
  • Payments associated with early termination of a tenancy (capped at the landlord's loss or the agent's reasonably incurred costs);
  • Where required, utilities (electricity, gas or other fuel, water, sewerage), communication services "telephone, internet, cable/satellite television), TV licence;
  • Council tax (payable to the billing authority);
  • Interest payments for the late payment of rent (up to 3% above Bank of England's annual percentage rate);
  • Reasonable costs for replacement of lost keys or other security devices;
  • Contractual damages in the event of the tenant's default of a tenancy agreement; and
  • Any other permitted payments under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 and regulations applicable at the relevant time.
For properties in Wales, the Renting Homes (Fees etc.) (Wales) Act 2019 means that in addition to rent, lettings agents can only charge tenants the following permitted payments
  • Holding deposits (a maximum of 1 week's rent);
  • Security deposits;
  • Where required, utilities (electricity, gas or other fuel, water, sewerage), communication services "telephone, internet, cable/satellite television), TV licence;
  • Council tax (payable to the billing authority);
  • Payments for the late payment of rent (where required under the tenancy agreement);
  • A breach of a term of the contract (where required under the tenancy agreement); and
  • Any other permitted payments under the Renting Homes (Fees etc.) (Wales) Act and regulations applicable at the relevant time.
Tenant protection In addition to publishing relevant fees, lettings agents are also required to publish details of:
  • the redress scheme they are a member of; and
  • the name of the approved or designated Client Money Protection scheme they are a member of (if any).

As well as paying the rent, you may also be required to make the following permitted payments either before, during or after your chosen tenancy.

Permitted Payments

Prior To Tenancy Start Date (Payable to The Robinson Jackson Group)
Holding Deposit: This is equivalent to one week s rent on the agreed monthly rental value and will be offset against the total move in monies due prior to move in.
Security Deposit: This is equivalent to 5 weeks rent on the agreed monthly rental value.

During The Tenancy Term (Payable to The Robinson Jackson Group)
Tenancy Amendment: A fee of £50.00 (incl. VAT) will apply if the tenant requests, and has approved, a variation, assignment or novation to the tenancy agreement.
Key Replacement: The cost price of the replacement of any lost key, key fob, security device or any other item that is required to access the property will be borne by you.
Early Termination: The landlord s cost in re-letting the property, in addition to the amount of rent due up until the start date of the new tenancy. These costs may not exceed the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy, or the actual cost of having to re-let the property.

During The Tenancy Term (Payable To The Provider)
Utilities: To include gas, water, sewerage, electricity or any other fuel unless otherwise included within the rent
Council Tax: Payable to the billing authority unless classed as exempt.
Communications: Telephone & Broadband Charges unless otherwise included within the rent
Cable/Satellite: Both the installation (upon approval from the landlord) and subscription to the relevant suppliers unless otherwise included in the rent.

Payment for damages in breach of the tenancy agreement or an agreement between The Robinson Jackson Group and a relevant person (tenant, guarantor or person acting on behalf of the tenant).

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Acceptance of any offer will be subject to contract, referencing and immigration checks. You will need to pay the Rent and Deposit that is due under a Tenancy Agreement, or where the landlord is offering the property with a deposit replacement guarantee product, and you wish to take up this option, you will need to provide proof that you have purchased such a product by providing us with a copy of the insurance certificate before a tenancy can start.

Referencing and Right to Rent Checks - You will be asked to complete an application form before referencing can be undertaken, you should also provide an original photographic Identification (e.g. passport, National ID card, VISA, resident permit, driving licence) and Proof of Residence (e.g. original utility bill, council tax bill or bank statement all of which much be less than 3 months old). The need for a guarantor may not become apparent until your referencing (including references for any joint tenants) has been completed. Where a guarantor is required an application form and photographic identification with proof of residence will be required.

Referencing will cover a check against the credit file and public records of the individual, an Anti-Money Laundering check, confirmation of employment and salary details, confirmation of previous tenancy details, right to rent checks, reporting the results of all those checks to your prospective landlord to see if your application is acceptable.

Tenant deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Deposits are limited to the equivalent of 5 weeks rent for new and renewed tenancies (or 6 weeks if the annual rent is £50,000 or more). This is calculated by dividing the annual rent by 52 and multiplying by 5 (or 6 if rent is £50,000 or more) and will be required to be paid at the start of the tenancy. This is subject to referencing.

Holding deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Holding Deposits are limited to the equivalent of one weeks rent. This is paid in order to reserve a property. This is calculated by multiplying the monthly rent by 12 to establish the annual rent, then dividing the annual rent by 52. The Holding Deposit will be required to be paid once your offer is accepted. You will be provided with the rules of when this is to be returned to you or retained by the agent before this payment is made.

Tenant Fees Act 2019 permits certain fees / charges to be made under the following circumstances:

Fee£ Inc. VATExplanation
Default fee for late payment of rentChargeable from 14 days arrears calculated on the interest at 3% above Bank of England base rate on the late payment of rent for each day that the payment is outstanding.
Loss of a key or other security deviceLandlords and letting agents can charge a tenant a fee to cover the cost of replacing the lost key or security device (e.g. fob, electronic device for garage doors / security gates).
Payment on variation, assignment or novation of a tenancy£50.00 When a tenant has requested it, landlords and letting agents can charge to vary, assign or replace a tenancy. Fee charge £50 (including VAT)
Payment on termination of a tenancyLandlords and letting agents can require a tenant to make a payment for an early termination (surrender) of the tenancy agreement at the tenants request.
Company application fee£100.00 £100 including VAT

Should you require further clarification, please ask us to explain these to you.

We are members of:

The Property Ombudsman Redress Scheme - C0008

ARLA/Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme - C0002080

greenSpaces.content:
Maidstone boasts numerous green spaces and trails.

**Parks and Green Spaces**

*   **Mote Park:** A large central park with a lake, woodland, and grassland, easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Whatman Park:** Forming part of the Maidstone Millennium River Park, it features a rose garden and playgrounds and is easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Teston Bridge Country Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park with playgrounds, conveniently located by car, though slightly further from the town centre.
*   **Clare Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park.  Accessibility from the town centre is not detailed.
*   **Cobtree Manor Park:** A smaller country park ideal for walks and picnics.  Town centre accessibility is unspecified.
*   **Brenchley Gardens:** A small formal garden near Maidstone East Station, easily accessible on foot.

**Walking Trails**

*   **Maidstone Millennium River Park:** A 10km riverside path along the River Medway, traversing the town centre and easily accessible on foot.
*   **North Downs Way National Trail:**  Sections of this long-distance trail are accessible by car, requiring a walk from the access point.

**Mountain Biking Trails**

*   Various mountain biking trails of differing lengths and difficulty levels are located around Maidstone, best accessed by car.  Precise accessibility details are unavailable, but further information can be found on AllTrails and Trailforks.

publicTransport.content:
Maidstone benefits from convenient transport links.

**Rail Services**

*   Three stations serve Maidstone: Maidstone East, Maidstone West, and Maidstone Barracks, all served by Southeastern.
*   Maidstone East provides direct trains to London Victoria (under an hour), Ashford International, and Canterbury.
*   Maidstone West offers services to Strood and Paddock Wood.

**Bus Services**

*   Arriva is the primary bus operator, supplemented by other providers.
*   Extensive bus routes connect Maidstone with neighbouring towns and villages, including park and ride facilities.

**Other Transport**

*   Taxis offer convenient local and regional travel.
*   Road access is facilitated by the M2 and M20 motorways, providing links to the M25 and other major routes.  Numerous roads connect Maidstone to surrounding areas.  However, congestion is anticipated during peak times.  Information on dedicated cycle lanes was unavailable.

(Information accurate as of January 2025)

barsAndRestaurants.content:
Maidstone's hospitality scene (accurate as of January 2025) includes a variety of restaurants, bars and cafes.

**Restaurants**

A selection of restaurants includes Argentinian cuisine at Buenos Aires Nights; The Romney at Mote House; Cast Iron Grill; family dining at Harvester - Running Horse; and The White Horse - Bearsted.  Other options include The Horseshoes @ East Farleigh; Taj Mahal Authentic Indian; Dylan's Nepalese and Indian; Wildwood Maidstone (European and global dishes); Vesuvias Restaurant; The Bierkeller - Maidstone; KalaRED Oriental Bar Restaurant; Thai Orchid Maidstone; Frederic Bistro; Wagamama Maidstone; Giggling Squid Maidstone; Market House Maidstone; Zizzi Maidstone; Patisserie Valerie Maidstone; Thaipalace; and Fifi's Brasserie.


**Bars**

Numerous bars are available, including MuMu; Bar Chocolate; Source Bar; The Brenchley; The Muggleton Inn; The Market House; The Stag; The Ashes Bar; The Bull Maidstone; and Ballin' Maidstone.


**Cafes**

Coffee and food are available at The Old Boat Cafe and Ivy Coffee House (which also offers cakes, pastries, breakfast and lunch).  Other cafes include The Little Old Toll House; Leah's; Aunt Sallys Kitchen (homemade breakfast and lunch); Baskerville's Coffee House (tea, sandwiches and pastries); Esquires Coffee - Maidstone (coffee, smoothies and snacks); and BBs Coffee & Muffins (muffins, coffee and savoury food).

schoolsAndNurseries.content:
Maidstone offers a range of schooling options, making it a potentially attractive location for families.  This information is accurate as of January 2025, but parents should verify details directly with the schools.

**Highly-Rated Primary Schools**

*   **Jubilee Primary School:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted.
*   **Tree Tops Primary Academy:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and well-regarded.
*   **Archbishop Courtenay Primary School:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and highly-regarded.

**Highly-Rated Secondary Schools**

*   **Maidstone Grammar School for Girls:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a leading girls' grammar school.
*   **Invicta Grammar School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; an excellent grammar school.
*   **Bower Grove School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a top-performing secondary school.
*   **Five Acre Wood School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; another highly-rated secondary school.

**Additional Schooling Options**

*   Maidstone has numerous other primary and secondary schools, many with positive Ofsted reports.
*   Three independent schools - OneSchool Global UK Maidstone Campus, Sutton Valence School, and MEPA Academy - provide fee-paying alternatives.

Always consult Ofsted reports and individual school websites for the most current information.

fitnessAndGyms.content:
Maidstone, UK, offers a variety of fitness facilities as of January 2025.

**Gyms**

Several gyms are available, including Welcome Gym, Village Gym, CORE The Gym, and PureGym.  Facilities typically include a range of equipment, classes, and amenities such as swimming pools, saunas, and steam rooms.  Many offer flexible membership options and free parking; however, specific details should be verified on individual gym websites.

**Yoga Studios**

A number of yoga studios operate in the town, such as Heavenly Fitness Studios, Yoga With Nicola, and Flowstone Studio.  These studios provide various yoga styles, including Hatha and Vinyasa.  Class schedules and specific styles offered vary, so it is advisable to check individual studio websites.

**Swimming Pools**

Swimming facilities are available at Maidstone Leisure Centre (with a learner, leisure, and main pool), Lockmeadow Health Club, Village Gym, and a 20m pool at Freedom Leisure.  Opening times differ between facilities, so please check the relevant websites for details.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Acceptance of any offer will be subject to contract, referencing and immigration checks. You will need to pay the Rent and Deposit that is due under a Tenancy Agreement, or where the landlord is offering the property with a deposit replacement guarantee product, and you wish to take up this option, you will need to provide proof that you have purchased such a product by providing us with a copy of the insurance certificate before a tenancy can start.

Referencing and Right to Rent Checks - You will be asked to complete an application form before referencing can be undertaken, you should also provide an original photographic Identification (e.g. passport, National ID card, VISA, resident permit, driving licence) and Proof of Residence (e.g. original utility bill, council tax bill or bank statement all of which much be less than 3 months old). The need for a guarantor may not become apparent until your referencing (including references for any joint tenants) has been completed. Where a guarantor is required an application form and photographic identification with proof of residence will be required.

Referencing will cover a check against the credit file and public records of the individual, an Anti-Money Laundering check, confirmation of employment and salary details, confirmation of previous tenancy details, right to rent checks, reporting the results of all those checks to your prospective landlord to see if your application is acceptable.

Tenant deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Deposits are limited to the equivalent of 5 weeks rent for new and renewed tenancies (or 6 weeks if the annual rent is £50,000 or more). This is calculated by dividing the annual rent by 52 and multiplying by 5 (or 6 if rent is £50,000 or more) and will be required to be paid at the start of the tenancy. This is subject to referencing.

Holding deposit - In England under the Tenant Fees Act 2019 Holding Deposits are limited to the equivalent of one weeks rent. This is paid in order to reserve a property. This is calculated by multiplying the monthly rent by 12 to establish the annual rent, then dividing the annual rent by 52. The Holding Deposit will be required to be paid once your offer is accepted. You will be provided with the rules of when this is to be returned to you or retained by the agent before this payment is made.

Tenant Fees Act 2019 permits certain fees / charges to be made under the following circumstances:

Fee£ Inc. VATExplanation
Default fee for late payment of rentChargeable from 14 days arrears calculated on the interest at 3% above Bank of England base rate on the late payment of rent for each day that the payment is outstanding.
Loss of a key or other security deviceLandlords and letting agents can charge a tenant a fee to cover the cost of replacing the lost key or security device (e.g. fob, electronic device for garage doors / security gates).
Payment on variation, assignment or novation of a tenancy£50.00 When a tenant has requested it, landlords and letting agents can charge to vary, assign or replace a tenancy. Fee charge £50 (including VAT)
Payment on termination of a tenancyLandlords and letting agents can require a tenant to make a payment for an early termination (surrender) of the tenancy agreement at the tenants request.
Company application fee£100.00 £100 including VAT

Should you require further clarification, please ask us to explain these to you.

We are members of:

The Property Ombudsman Redress Scheme - C0008

ARLA/Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme - C0002080
