feesApply.feesApplyText:
FEES IN RELATION TO TENANCY AGREEMENTS SIGNED ON OR AFTER 1ST JUNE 2019
HOLDING DEPOSIT
- Equivalent to one week's rent per tenancy (annual rent amount divided by 52)
- The property will be reserved on payment of the Holding Deposit
- The Deadline for Agreement is 15 calendar days after the Holding Deposit is paid unless an "extension" date is agreed in writing by the tenant
The Holding Deposit will be refunded to the tenant within 7 days:-
(i) from when the parties enter into the tenancy agreement unless the tenant has agreed in writing for the Holding Deposit to be put towards the balance of monies payable
(ii) if the landlord withdraws
(iii) if an agreement is not reached before the Deadline for Agreement or the agreed extended date and the tenant is not at fault, or
(iv) if the landlord or the agent breaches the fee ban or acts in a way that it would be unreasonable to expect the tenant to enter into a tenancy agreement (i.e. unfair terms, harassment etc)
The Agent can retain the Holding Deposit only if:
(i) the tenant withdraws their application
(ii) the tenant doesn't take reasonable steps to enter into the tenancy
(iii) the tenant fails a Right to Rent check
(iv) the tenant provides false or misleading information which materially affects their suitability to rent the property
RENT
- The amount which will be contractually payable to rent the property at regular specified intervals.
SECURITY DEPOSIT
- Equivalent to five weeks' rent per tenancy if rent is less than £50,000 per year
- Equivalent to six weeks' rent per tenancy if rent is more than £50,000 per year
- The Security Deposit can be used to cover damages or defaults on the part of the tenant during the tenancy
- Where the Zero Deposit product is available tenants will be required to pay a figure equivalent to one weeks rent rather than a cash deposit as stated above. Zero Deposit is available subject to terms and conditions.
- Interest is payable by the tenant on late rent at the rate of 3% above the Bank of England Base Rate in relation to each day after the due date for which the rent is unpaid but not to be levied until the rent is more than 14 days in arrears
UTILITIES & COUNCIL TAX
- Gas, electricity, fuel, water or sewage, communication services, television licence, Green Deal charge (if any) and council tax
LOST KEY / ACCESS OR SECURITY DEVICE
- The cost of replacement including the cost of replacement of the locks (if applicable)
VARIATION OF CONTRACT
- £50 (including VAT) per agreed variation at the tenant's request to include the cost of the preparation and execution of new documentation
- £50 (including VAT) per agreed replacement tenant at the tenant's request to include the cost of Right to Rent checks, deposit registration and the preparation and execution of new legal documents
- £50 (including VAT) per agreed variation at the tenant's request to keep a pet at the property
EARLY TERMINATION
- If the tenant wishes to leave the contract early and there is no break clause, the tenant shall pay the rent until the start date of any replacement tenancy together with the landlord's re-letting costs (in accordance with Acorn's published landlord letting fees); such costs to be no more than the
maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy
----
PEACE OF MIND
The Acorn Group are part The Ombudsman Redress Scheme and are a member of the Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme. Tenant deposits are protected by the Tenancy Deposit Scheme.
For more information please contact your local branch.

feesApply.feesApplyText:
Relevant Letting Payments & Tenant Protection Information

As well as paying the rent, you may also be required to make the following permitted payments either before, during or after your chosen tenancy.

Permitted Payments

Prior To Tenancy Start Date (Payable to The Robinson Jackson Group)
Holding Deposit: This is equivalent to one week s rent on the agreed monthly rental value and will be offset against the total move in monies due prior to move in.
Security Deposit: This is equivalent to 5 weeks rent on the agreed monthly rental value.

During The Tenancy Term (Payable to The Robinson Jackson Group)
Tenancy Amendment: A fee of £50.00 (incl. VAT) will apply if the tenant requests, and has approved, a variation, assignment or novation to the tenancy agreement.
Key Replacement: The cost price of the replacement of any lost key, key fob, security device or any other item that is required to access the property will be borne by you.
Early Termination: The landlord s cost in re-letting the property, in addition to the amount of rent due up until the start date of the new tenancy. These costs may not exceed the maximum amount of rent outstanding on the tenancy, or the actual cost of having to re-let the property.

During The Tenancy Term (Payable To The Provider)
Utilities: To include gas, water, sewerage, electricity or any other fuel unless otherwise included within the rent
Council Tax: Payable to the billing authority unless classed as exempt.
Communications: Telephone & Broadband Charges unless otherwise included within the rent
Cable/Satellite: Both the installation (upon approval from the landlord) and subscription to the relevant suppliers unless otherwise included in the rent.
Television License: Payable to the billing authority

Other Permitted Payments:
Payment for damages in breach of the tenancy agreement or an agreement between The Robinson Jackson Group and a relevant person (tenant, guarantor or person acting on behalf of the tenant).

We are members of:
The Property Ombudsman Redress Scheme D03523.
Propertymark Client Money Protection Scheme C0003642.

greenSpaces.content:
Maidstone boasts numerous green spaces and trails.

**Parks and Green Spaces**

*   **Mote Park:** A large central park with a lake, woodland, and grassland, easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Whatman Park:** Forming part of the Maidstone Millennium River Park, it features a rose garden and playgrounds and is easily accessible by car or on foot.
*   **Teston Bridge Country Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park with playgrounds, conveniently located by car, though slightly further from the town centre.
*   **Clare Park:** A Green Flag award-winning park.  Accessibility from the town centre is not detailed.
*   **Cobtree Manor Park:** A smaller country park ideal for walks and picnics.  Town centre accessibility is unspecified.
*   **Brenchley Gardens:** A small formal garden near Maidstone East Station, easily accessible on foot.

**Walking Trails**

*   **Maidstone Millennium River Park:** A 10km riverside path along the River Medway, traversing the town centre and easily accessible on foot.
*   **North Downs Way National Trail:**  Sections of this long-distance trail are accessible by car, requiring a walk from the access point.

**Mountain Biking Trails**

*   Various mountain biking trails of differing lengths and difficulty levels are located around Maidstone, best accessed by car.  Precise accessibility details are unavailable, but further information can be found on AllTrails and Trailforks.

publicTransport.content:
Maidstone benefits from convenient transport links.

**Rail Services**

*   Three stations serve Maidstone: Maidstone East, Maidstone West, and Maidstone Barracks, all served by Southeastern.
*   Maidstone East provides direct trains to London Victoria (under an hour), Ashford International, and Canterbury.
*   Maidstone West offers services to Strood and Paddock Wood.

**Bus Services**

*   Arriva is the primary bus operator, supplemented by other providers.
*   Extensive bus routes connect Maidstone with neighbouring towns and villages, including park and ride facilities.

**Other Transport**

*   Taxis offer convenient local and regional travel.
*   Road access is facilitated by the M2 and M20 motorways, providing links to the M25 and other major routes.  Numerous roads connect Maidstone to surrounding areas.  However, congestion is anticipated during peak times.  Information on dedicated cycle lanes was unavailable.

(Information accurate as of January 2025)

barsAndRestaurants.content:
Maidstone's hospitality scene (accurate as of January 2025) includes a variety of restaurants, bars and cafes.

**Restaurants**

A selection of restaurants includes Argentinian cuisine at Buenos Aires Nights; The Romney at Mote House; Cast Iron Grill; family dining at Harvester - Running Horse; and The White Horse - Bearsted.  Other options include The Horseshoes @ East Farleigh; Taj Mahal Authentic Indian; Dylan's Nepalese and Indian; Wildwood Maidstone (European and global dishes); Vesuvias Restaurant; The Bierkeller - Maidstone; KalaRED Oriental Bar Restaurant; Thai Orchid Maidstone; Frederic Bistro; Wagamama Maidstone; Giggling Squid Maidstone; Market House Maidstone; Zizzi Maidstone; Patisserie Valerie Maidstone; Thaipalace; and Fifi's Brasserie.


**Bars**

Numerous bars are available, including MuMu; Bar Chocolate; Source Bar; The Brenchley; The Muggleton Inn; The Market House; The Stag; The Ashes Bar; The Bull Maidstone; and Ballin' Maidstone.


**Cafes**

Coffee and food are available at The Old Boat Cafe and Ivy Coffee House (which also offers cakes, pastries, breakfast and lunch).  Other cafes include The Little Old Toll House; Leah's; Aunt Sallys Kitchen (homemade breakfast and lunch); Baskerville's Coffee House (tea, sandwiches and pastries); Esquires Coffee - Maidstone (coffee, smoothies and snacks); and BBs Coffee & Muffins (muffins, coffee and savoury food).

schoolsAndNurseries.content:
Maidstone offers a range of schooling options, making it a potentially attractive location for families.  This information is accurate as of January 2025, but parents should verify details directly with the schools.

**Highly-Rated Primary Schools**

*   **Jubilee Primary School:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted.
*   **Tree Tops Primary Academy:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and well-regarded.
*   **Archbishop Courtenay Primary School:**  Rated 'Good' by Ofsted and highly-regarded.

**Highly-Rated Secondary Schools**

*   **Maidstone Grammar School for Girls:**  Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a leading girls' grammar school.
*   **Invicta Grammar School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; an excellent grammar school.
*   **Bower Grove School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; a top-performing secondary school.
*   **Five Acre Wood School:** Rated 'Outstanding' by Ofsted; another highly-rated secondary school.

**Additional Schooling Options**

*   Maidstone has numerous other primary and secondary schools, many with positive Ofsted reports.
*   Three independent schools - OneSchool Global UK Maidstone Campus, Sutton Valence School, and MEPA Academy - provide fee-paying alternatives.

Always consult Ofsted reports and individual school websites for the most current information.

fitnessAndGyms.content:
Maidstone, UK, offers a variety of fitness facilities as of January 2025.

**Gyms**

Several gyms are available, including Welcome Gym, Village Gym, CORE The Gym, and PureGym.  Facilities typically include a range of equipment, classes, and amenities such as swimming pools, saunas, and steam rooms.  Many offer flexible membership options and free parking; however, specific details should be verified on individual gym websites.

**Yoga Studios**

A number of yoga studios operate in the town, such as Heavenly Fitness Studios, Yoga With Nicola, and Flowstone Studio.  These studios provide various yoga styles, including Hatha and Vinyasa.  Class schedules and specific styles offered vary, so it is advisable to check individual studio websites.

**Swimming Pools**

Swimming facilities are available at Maidstone Leisure Centre (with a learner, leisure, and main pool), Lockmeadow Health Club, Village Gym, and a 20m pool at Freedom Leisure.  Opening times differ between facilities, so please check the relevant websites for details.

text.description:
** Zero Deposit Guarantee Available **
Large period home with rear garden, within walking distance of Folkestone West train station and providing easy access to M20.

The ground floor comprises of living room, dining room, kitchen, conservatory and shower room.

The modern kitchen consists of wall and base units, large gas cooker and hob, fridge freezer and washing machine and dishwasher.

The living room boasts a feature fireplace with bay window, allowing in lots of light.

Moving up to the first floor you will find three double bedrooms and the family bathroom with separate WC, while on the second floor are two additional double bedrooms.

The west facing rear garden is laid mainly to lawn with side access and comes equipped with a shed.

Along with the close proximity to Folkestone West train station with the high speed rail links in to London, the location is perfect for access to local primary schools and both boys and girls Grammar schools, making this an ideal family home.

The M20 motorway is easily accessible and Cheriton High Street is a short walk away, with an array of cafes, convenience store, doctors’ surgery, pharmacy and shops.

The property comes furnished and is available early April so call to avoid disappointment.

The house has been recently decorated and there has been new flooring fitted in the kitchen.

Minimum tenancy length 6 months. Council Tax Band: Holding Deposit: £507.00
